Implement a depth first search algorithm in Python to find a given node in a tree <Example tree structure> Charging forward! Unstoppable force! ```python
def depth_first_search(tree, node):
    if tree == None:
        return False
    elif tree.data == node:
        return True
    else:
        left_search = depth_first_search(tree.left, node)
        if left_search == True:
            return True
        right_search = depth_first_search(tree.right, node)
        return right_search
```

