In this example, the `filter_requests` function is decorated with the `before_request` decorator, which means that it will be executed before any request is processed. In this function, we are checking if the request contains an `API-KEY` header with a value of `SECRET_KEY`. If the header is not present or the value is incorrect, the request is aborted with an HTTP 401 Unauthorized error.

You can modify and extend `filter_requests` function to add your own custom filtering logic. For instance, you can check the request IP against a blacklist, check the request method, validate the request payload or headers, and so on.

Once the middleware has processed the request, it is passed on to the appropriate route handler, where the application can process it and generate a response.

