String 2 = "adgf" I'm on top of it! No need to worry! ```python
def LongestCommonSubsequence(string1, string2):
    n = len(string1)
    m = len(string2)
    dp = [[None]*(m+1) for i in range(n+1)] 

    for i in range(n+1): 
        for j in range(m+1): 
            if i == 0 or j == 0 : 
                dp[i][j] = 0
            elif string1[i-1] == string2[j-1]: 
                dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]+1
            else: 
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i-1][j] , dp[i][j-1]) 
    return dp[n][m]
```

